Yang Haodong is delivering a speech on the spirit of the 19th National Congress of the Communist Party of China and the Provincial Party Congress at Malan Mountain.
Draw strength for progress from the 100-year history of the party's struggle.
Hunan Daily, December 10th News (All Media Reporter Gong Bo Wei): According to the unified arrangement of the provincial party committee, on the morning of December 10th, Yang Haodong, a standing committee member and minister of the Propaganda Department of the Provincial Party Committee, made an interactive speech at the Malan Mountain video and cultural park. He deeply studied and implemented the spirit of the 19th National Congress of the Communist Party of China and studied and implemented General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech and instructions for Hunan, as well as the spirit of the 12th Provincial Party Congress.
From three perspectives, ideal beliefs and original mission, self-revolution and youth in the party, and the party's leadership and theory, Yang Haodong combined his own insights and personal experiences to thoroughly and systematically explain the core meaning and practical requirements of the congress spirit.
He pointed out that to study the congress spirit and General Secretary Xi Jinping's important speech and instructions for Hunan, as well as the provincial party congress spirit, it is necessary to combine them and integrate them into a comprehensive understanding. This will enhance the conscious recognition of the "two establishements," the conscious actions to maintain them, and the unswerving determination to move forward in the direction guided by General Secretary Xi Jinping.
In the interaction and exchange session, representatives of grassroots cadres, enterprise representatives, and youth representatives asked questions about the relationship between three historical resolutions, how to understand the decisive significance of "two established", how cultural enterprises grasp the orientation, and how young people in the new era draw strength from the hundred-year party history. Yang Haodong answered one by one with popular language and vivid examples. He sincerely told young party members to draw strength from the hundred-year struggle history of the party, to closely unite around the central party leadership, to be unswerving and follow the party, and to write responsibility and responsibility with their youth devotion.